<a href="www.greypathfinders.com/daoc.htm">Glas Cinneadh</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaithcaidh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caith Caidh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/19/01 7:28:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1375.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> Well, I wouldn't say &quot;well rounded&quot; exactly Nim...  More that everything we can do is equally ineffectual.  Our spells are somewhat of a joke.  Sure I can pull with it, but that's not why I chose to be nightshade after reading the class descriptions, before ever logging in.  Disguise isn't in yet, and in order to be as effective as I want to be at certain things, I can't afford to be well rounded.    <br>
Took a shot at a yellow con dwarf healer today, frontal PA, with a decent sized sword.  Took maybe 20% off.  Archer probably would have had him dropped in four shots.  As is, I was dead before I could get more than 2 or 3 swings in (He had a group with him)...<br>
Of course, two days ago, I would have been bladeturned, so this is still an improvement.<br>
<br>
Seriously, for my money given the difficulty of setting up, we should be able to take out any yellow.  Now, sure, that one was in a large group, but I sincerely doubt I would have come out on top even had he been solo.  My first shot barely scratched him.  Hell, I've been hit my blue con mobs for a larger percentage of damage.<br>
Perhaps for RvR our initial CS chain should take off a percentage of max health (Random, but modified by con, etc.  I.e. on a high purple if we even land we take off perhaps 5% health on a full landed PA chain, perhaps less, while on a yellow a full landed chain should average around 100%.  I.e. We should have a good shot at dropping any yellow con in three shots.  I'd even take a trade off where our chain could be interrupted if we're hit from another source during that initial chain...  That would make the element of surprise all the more critical - A group that reacts quickly MIGHT be able to save that healer, but the healer him or herself striking back shouldn't interrupt (I'd go as far as to say that we should be nearly immune to insta stun messes from a yellow target - provided that we've started our chain on them.)  <br>
Yeah, I know if anything like this was ever put in, we'd suddenly be hearing cries of &quot;Nerf the Nightshades&quot;.  @#%$ I wish there was a reason for people to cry that though, I really do.  My score for today was one grey troll, twice (They didn't learn.  He was grouped with a yellow tank, so I considered him fair game.  If his friend got to me, I was toast).  I should have been able to take out his friend instead of him.<br>
I mean, seriously... Who's immune to a blade across the throat?<br>
<br>
